<subSubSection id="C5177CE947878B745F01B06BC7D3DA6E" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="0C2924EA36B29514A606DFD82AFE05F4" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C9B79640A4B3AFA67D0B2328F19815B" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
A range-restricted Balkan endemic with a very limited distribution in Greece, where only two records from the mountains of Voras (NC Greece) and Falakro (NE Greece) are known (
<bibRefCitation id="3F4C791B544A35DDE93C4523AD433E6B" author="Raus, T." journalOrPublisher="Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7669266" refString="Raus, T., 1991. Mountain Flora of Greece 2. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" title="Mountain Flora of Greece 2" year="1991">Raus 1991</bibRefCitation>
). This is the third Greek population (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0F3AFE08375EE37446A48241C5A686FB" captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F7677688" captionText="Figure 20. Pedicularis orthantha from Mt. Rodopi (photo: P. Doumas)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/640570" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">20</figureCitation>
) and the easternmost border of the species distribution in the country.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
